Route 53 is AWS’s DNS service
Amazon S3 Scalable storage in the AWS cloud.
You store your data in containers called buckets
Amazon Elastic Block Store (EBS) Network attached storage volumes for your virtual servers.
Amazon Glacier Low-cost archival storage. - used for archiving - you create vaults (like buckets in S3)
Instances are virtual servers that can run applications
Spot instances - bid for a price on your instance (cheaper by 90%)
Each region contains multiple distinct locations called Availability Zones
To make the subnet public, let’s add an Internet Gateway and route all outbound traffic through it
etcd is a distributed, consistent key-value store used for storing shared configuration and information in a cluster
Multiple availability zones = different data centers
old type scaling is vertical - cloud scaling is horizontal scale out
Cloudwatch - Monitoring via alarms
cloudfront - webserver cache
Autoscaling Cloudformation - templating a full stack of VM's
Amazon SNS - Mails alerts
Amazon SES - Mailing system for mass emails (like authsmtp.com)

